<DOC><DOCNO> AP890512-0099 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-12-89 1101EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-BRF--MinisterGuilty     05-12 0171</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Minister Guilty,0175</SECOND><HEAD>Popular Minister Found Guilty of Abusing Former Foster Child</HEAD><DATELINE>MARKHAM, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A community activist and clergyman fromChicago's South Side has been convicted of sexually abusing ateen-age foster son.   The Cook County jury, which heard eight days of testimony,deliberated more than seven hours before returning the verdictThursday night against the Rev. Paul Hall, a licensed foster parentand founder of a boys club.   He was found guilty of two counts of criminal sexual assault andfive counts of aggravated criminal sexual abuse. He was acquittedon two aggravated abuse charges.   Hall was indicted last year for sexual assaults against two boyswho lived at his home in South Holland.   The trial involved only one of the youths, who said he wasrepeatedly molested over 19 months. Hall, who testified in his owndefense, denied the charges. His attorney said the conviction wouldbe appealed.   Hall remains free on bond until sentencing June 7. He faces 15years to 30 years in prison.</TEXT></DOC>